# free_agent proxy configuration.
#
# Copy this file to `.env` and adjust as needed:
#     cp .env.example .env
#
# `run_fa_proxy.sh` loads `.env` automatically (if present) and exports every
# variable below into the proxy's environment before launching it. Values here
# are the proxy's own defaults, shown explicitly for convenience.

# --- Upstream Ollama server ------------------------------------------------
# The Ollama the proxy forwards to (both the agent loop and its own
# summary/label calls). Local by default; set it to a remote host to use a
# remote Ollama, e.g. OLLAMA_BASE_URL=http://192.168.1.50:11434
OLLAMA_BASE_URL=http://localhost:11434
# Set to 1 for a REMOTE Ollama: skips the local install/serve/pull dance in
# ./FreeAgent while still installing the Python deps. (FA_SKIP_INSTALL=1
# skips both deps and the Ollama setup.)
#FA_SKIP_OLLAMA=0

# --- Model selection (single source of truth) ------------------------------
# FA_MODEL drives BOTH the main agent loop and the proxy's own summary/label +
# file-ledger calls. The proxy stamps FA_MODEL onto every main-agent request,
# so the model id configured in opencode.json is just a cosmetic placeholder —
# change the model HERE and restart the proxy; you never touch opencode.json.
FA_MODEL=qwen3.6:35b
# Optional: run the summary/label calls on a *different* model than the agent.
# Leave unset to use FA_MODEL for both (the common case).
#FA_MAIN_MODEL=qwen3.6:35b

# --- Reasoning level (optional) --------------------------------------------
# Reasoning/thinking effort for the MAIN AGENT loop (the model answering you).
# Values:
#   (unset / blank) : leave the model's own default — nothing is sent
#   off             : disable reasoning
#   low | medium | high : effort level (mapped to each provider's own field —
#                         reasoning_effort for Ollama's /v1 API, think for the
#                         native API, a thinking budget for Anthropic)
FA_REASONING=medium
# FA_MAIN_REASONING is a kept-for-compat alias for FA_REASONING (agent loop).
FA_MAIN_REASONING=medium
# Reasoning for the internal summary/label/file-ledger calls. These run BLOCKING,
# before the agent is called, and their thinking is discarded — so this defaults
# to OFF even when the agent uses reasoning (turning it up just adds latency and
# timeout risk). Leave unset unless you have a specific reason.
#FA_SUMM_REASONING=off

# --- Where archive/, state.json, and audit.log are written -----------------
# A leading ~ is expanded (both the shell and the library expand it).
FA_STORAGE_ROOT=~/.free_agent

# --- Recency window --------------------------------------------------------
# Keep this many of the most recent completed turns in the live context as
# their full text (text messages only — tool use and file reads are dropped);
# every older turn falls back to its one-line summary. 0 reproduces the
# original behavior (each completed turn is summarized as soon as it finishes).
FA_NUM_FULL_TEXT_TURNS=1

# --- Continue on empty reply -----------------------------------------------
# Some models occasionally return an empty final message (no content, no tool
# calls), which shows up as a blank assistant turn in OpenCode. When enabled,
# the proxy transparently re-asks the model with a "please continue." nudge and
# returns the non-empty result. The nudge lives only inside the retry request —
# it never reaches OpenCode's transcript or free_agent's summaries.
FA_CONTINUE_ON_EMPTY=1
# Max retries before giving up and forwarding the empty response as-is.
FA_CONTINUE_MAX=2
# The nudge text sent on an empty reply.
#FA_CONTINUE_MSG=please continue.

# --- Tool filtering --------------------------------------------------------
# Drop/keep tools from the host's tool set before they reach the model.
# FA_TOOLS_DENY: comma-separated tool names to drop. Defaults to "glob".
#   Set it empty (FA_TOOLS_DENY=) to disable the default and pass every tool.
#   Add more like: FA_TOOLS_DENY=glob,ls,webfetch
FA_TOOLS_DENY=glob,task
# FA_TOOLS_ALLOW: comma-separated allowlist — keep ONLY these tools. When set it
#   takes precedence over FA_TOOLS_DENY. Stricter but riskier (removing a tool
#   the host still references in a prior tool_call can make some backends error).
#   Leave unset unless you want a hard whitelist. Example:
#FA_TOOLS_ALLOW=read,edit,write,grep,bash

# --- Audit dumps -----------------------------------------------------------
# Set to 1 to enable; any other value (blank / 0) disables. See the README's
# "Caveats & tuning" section for exactly what each one writes.
#
# Exact messages sent to the main model at the start of each turn.
FA_AUDIT_OUTBOUND=1
# Exact messages the main model returned during each turn's tool loop.
FA_AUDIT_INBOUND=0
# Complete interleaved turn transcript (in-flight msgs + tool calls + results).
FA_AUDIT_FULL=1

# --- System-prompt override ------------------------------------------------
# Replace the host's (OpenCode's) system prompt with your own. This only
# touches the main agent loop — OpenCode's auxiliary title/summary prompts and
# the tool definitions are always forwarded untouched.
#
# Master switch: nothing is overridden unless this is exactly 1, so you can
# leave a prompt configured below and flip it on/off from here.
FA_SYSTEM_OVERRIDE=1
# Your replacement prompt. Use FA_SYSTEM_PROMPT_FILE to point at a file (takes
# precedence and is easier for multi-line prompts), or FA_SYSTEM_PROMPT inline.
# A relative path is resolved against the repo root (not the launch cwd), so the
# bundled example just works; ~ and absolute paths are honored too.
FA_SYSTEM_PROMPT_FILE=./system_prompt/my_system_prompt.md
#FA_SYSTEM_PROMPT=You are a terse, senior engineer. Prefer minimal diffs.
# How your text combines with the host's prompt:
#   replace : swap the host's system prompt for yours (default)
#   prefix  : your text, then the host's prompt (keeps OpenCode's env/tool notes)
#   previx_env :L your text, then ONLY the <env>...</env> block from the host (if present)
#   suffix  : the host's prompt, then your text
FA_SYSTEM_MODE=prefix_env

# --- Proxy bind address (consumed by run_fa_proxy.sh, not the proxy) -------
FA_PROXY_HOST=127.0.0.1
FA_PROXY_PORT=49786

# --- Launch an interactive CLI alongside the proxy -------------------------
# When set to 1, ./FreeAgent starts the proxy in the BACKGROUND, waits
# for it to come up, then hands this same terminal to an interactive OpenCode
# session (`opencode`). Quitting OpenCode tears the proxy down too, so one
# terminal window = one full session. When 0 (default) the proxy runs in the
# foreground as before and you start `opencode` yourself in another terminal.
FA_LAUNCH_CLI=1
# Command used to start that CLI session. Change it if `opencode` isn't on your
# PATH under that name, or to pass flags / launch a different client.
#FA_CLI_CMD=opencode
# Which project folder the CLI opens. Leave unset to be asked interactively at
# launch (default = the folder you ran ./FreeAgent from). A positional
# argument — `./FreeAgent ~/code/my-app` — overrides this. Proxy sessions
# are keyed per OpenCode conversation, so separate conversations stay isolated
# (their compacted histories and recall archives never cross) no matter which
# folder you open.
#FA_CLI_DIR=~/code/my-app
# When no folder is set above, a native "choose folder" dialog pops up (macOS:
# osascript; Linux: zenity or kdialog). Set FA_CLI_PICKER=none to skip the popup
# and just type the path at a text prompt (useful over SSH / headless).
#FA_CLI_PICKER=auto
# Text shown in your terminal's window/tab title bar for the whole CLI session.
# OpenCode has no config for its own banner text, so this is how we surface
# branding alongside it — the title survives OpenCode's full-screen TUI. Only
# applies when FA_LAUNCH_CLI=1, and only when output is an interactive terminal.
# Leave it commented to use the built-in default (shown below); set it to your
# own text to override, or set it empty (FA_TERM_TITLE=) to disable the title.
#FA_TERM_TITLE=Empromptu FreeAgent - The Free, Optimized Coding Agent
